data.title: Jack
data.text: This is your average Jack in the Box fast food place. it is along a busy state highway that runs N/S through the valley. Service was average also.

data.title: It's Jack
data.text: Breakfast at Jack's, simple but worked for us.  The silver dollar pancakes were good, scrambled eggs and bacon were average. Breakfast all day is nice.  The pop machine allows many choices of flavourings.

data.title: Just as Jack in the Box should be!
data.text: Nice change from typical east coast fast food standards i.e. Micky D's, etc. Clean, friendly & good burgers & fries.

data.title: Late night, long wait, below average quality
data.text: I only went there out of desperation. I actually like Jack in the Box, but I thought this one was sub-par.

data.title: Fast food
data.text: It's fast food. Burgers. Fries. Soft drinks. Drive through. About what you'd expect. It is close to the hotel.

data.title: when ya gotta have a greasy taco
data.text: Can't beat 2 tacos for $.99, so why not 4? A real gut bomb and blast from the past as there are no JITB in Montana that I know of. Definitely hit the spot after a long day on the road.

data.title: Good food
data.text: I ordered a to go order and got Chicken Nuggets and Chicken Strips. They gave me several extra sauces as I was taking the one order of Nuggets to 3 children to share.  The chicken had a light batter, I prefer a little thicker one but it was good, a little more brown on the outside than I thought would be good but it turned out it was very tasty. This Jack in the box was on Pines St.

data.title: Reusable refusal!
data.text: My food want bad...but I am befuddled about my Jack in the Box experience today... I went through the drive through at about 1:00 pm, it wasn't very busy, I ordered my burger, and when I got to the window, I asked the nice lady who was working if I could get her to put water in my reusable cup. You see, I am a green minded person and I know that fast food trash accounts for 33% of our litter problem, so I prefer to use my reusable cup instead of asking for water in a paper cup. The lady at the window told me she is not allowed to fill my cup....but could give me a paper cup of water to fill it myself....THAT DEFEATS THE PURPOSE OF MY PLASTIC CUP!!! Someone said its to ensure I wont get sick from the water....BAH! its the same water...no matter the cup. Come on JACK IN THE BOX! I love your burgers, but you cant keep this up. I don't want to create garbage, and you should be willing to help reduce it.
